cape Room desires, such as perhaps the combination to a lock or door.  Or perhaps a 4 letter word that is needed in the next puzzle challenge.\r\n\r\nThe box 6” x 6” x 3” box  is solid and will not open.  It is also empty.  On the bottom size is a hole large enough to easily fit a finger.  Around the  outer sides of the box are the digits 0 to 9 with their braille equivalent.  Your quests will no doubt wonder what an empty box is for!\r\n\r\nThere is a secret inside the box though…\r\n\r\nThe bottom of the box has the numbers 1 to 4 laser engraved at 90 degree intervals around the center hole.   If one sticks a finger in the box and feels under each of these locations, a series of raised dots can be felt.  Eureka!\r\n\r\nHowever, now those raised dots must be interpreted to numbers using just your finger senses combined with braille table glued to the sides of the box.\r\n\r\nThe design was the result of an Escape Room owner asking us if we could build something so that a blind person could actively participate in the Escape Room Experience.  Though a sighted person can solve this; the edge would certainly go the person who can read braille with their fingertips!\r\n\r\nFor additional information on customizing your Escape Room and this item please visit our Custom Work Page.\r\n\r\n','BRAILLE BOX - ESCAPE ROOM PUZZLE AND PROP','','publish','open','closed','','braille-box-escape-room-puzzle-and-prop','','','2017-01-22 11:43:46','2017-01-22 11:43:46','',0,'http://localhost/escaperoom/?post_type=product&#038;p=90',0,'product','',0),(91,1,'2017-01-14 15:10:58','2017-01-14 15:10:58','A clever and fun way to offer Gift Cards for your Escape Rooms. Cash out is a puzzle which will lock a gift card behind the clear plexiglass plate providing a visual incentive to solve the puzzle. \r\n\r\nIf you are interested in having the puzzle engraved with your website or Escape Room','CASH OUT - ESCAPE ROOM GIFT CARD PUZZLE','If you are interested in having the puzzle engraved with your website or Escape Room','publish','open','closed','','cash-out-escape-room-gift-card-puzzle','','','2017-01-30 17:38:17','2017-01-30 17:38:17','',0,'http://localhost/escaperoom/?post_type=product&#038;p=91',0,'product','',1),(93,1,'2017-01-14 15:15:36','2017-01-14 15:15:36','Hardwood construction with gears cut from ¼” thick wood. All letters and text are deeply laser engraved into the wood. Base is USA Hickory.  The gears turn on alloy steel pins.  Measures about 13\" x 5\" x 1.3\"\r\n\r\nIf you would like to purchase additional gears please visit this page.\r\n\r\n© 2016 Creative Crafthouse  Made in  Hudson, FL, USA\r\n\r\nA summary of how to use the machine is listed below.  I recommend you watch the video to make it clear.  It’s a very fast and easy process once you learn how to do it.\r\n\r\n1.Define an initial gear order.  Each gear is labeled by A, B, or C. Set the gears on the pins in the order you select.\r\n\r\n2. Define the initial Key, 3 characters long.   The Key defines the gear orientations.  Arrange each gear such the pointer on the board points to the key letter on the Gear.  If the Key was DOG for instance, the first gear would be set to D at the arrow.  The second gear to O at the arrow; and the third gear to G at the arrow.  The The key can be embedded in the message or for better security it can be communicated separately.\r\n\r\n3. Write the english text that you wish to encode in the lines and boxes marked “Text” on the provided worksheet; or just on a piece of paper if you don’t have a worksheet.  Do not use spaces or punctuation.\r\n\r\n4. The right side gear is the English Text wheel.  To begin encryption, find the 1st letter of your message and align it with the arrow next to this wheel.  Read the corresponding letter that appears at the top arrow of the gear 1, which is the left gear on the board.  Write this letter in the “Code” block of your worksheet right below the letter you just encoded.    Next set the English Test wheel to the second letter of your message.  Read the encoded letter on the 2nd (middle) gear.  Repeat this process of going from the left gear(1) to the center gear (2).\r\n\r\n','ENIGMA MACHINES','A complex form of encryption which will add an extremely challenging element to your Escape Room. We have several versions which vary in degrees of difficulty to','publish','open','closed','','enigma-machines','','','2017-01-14 15:15:36','2017-01-14 15:15:36','',0,'http://localhost/escaperoom/?post_type=product&#038;p=93',0,'product','',0),(94,1,'2017-01-14 15:19:16','2017-01-14 15:19:16','A marriage of two of our most stunning Escape Room Props and Puzzles: The Key Maze & The Donation Box. The Donation Lock Box needs a Key which conveniently finds itself trapped within the Key Maze.\r\n\r\nThe Key Maze is available in two Styles: Wood and Acrylic.','DONATION BOX AND KEY MAZE SYNERGY SET','Various Escape Room Maze Puzzles available for purchase online. Find handmade Key Mazes, Magnet Mazes, Disc Mazes perfect for providing a unique Escape Room experience','publish','open','closed','','donation-box-and-key-maze-synergy-set','','','2017-01-30 17:31:34','2017-01-30 17:31:34','',0,'http://localhost/escaperoom/?post_type=product&#038;p=94',0,'product','',0),(95,1,'2017-01-14 15:22:30','2017-01-14 15:22:30','The clues engraved on the bottom of each piece are fully customizable. They can be a string of numbers, short message, or even symbols of your choosing (Hieroglyphs, Runes, etc...) One of the pieces has a single slice cut out with a single circle inlayed. The other has two slices cut with two pieces of Alder inlayed. These are clues indicating the order your Escape Room players need to determine the clue(s)\r\n\r\nImportant: Please make note of what you want engraved on the bottom of each piece in the \"Special Instructions for Seller\" box at checkout. There will be no additional cost for numbers/letters. Images/Symbols may cost more depending on the amount of work involved preparing 